# ofxQTMRT

openFrameworks addon for receiving motion-capture data from **Qualisys Track Manager (QTM)** over the **QTM Real-Time (RT) protocol**.

It wraps the official [`qualisys_cpp_sdk`](https://github.com/qualisys/qualisys_cpp_sdk) (bundled and compiled from source) behind an ofxNatNet-style API, so porting existing OptiTrack/NatNet projects is mostly a search-and-replace.

## Status

- ✅ 6DOF rigid bodies (position + rotation as `ofMatrix4x4`)
- ✅ 3D labeled markers
- ✅ 3D unlabeled markers
- ✅ Background receive thread + double-buffered, lock-free reads on the main thread
- ✅ Automatic reconnect
- ⏳ Skeletons, analog, force plates — not yet exposed (reachable via `getProtocol()`)

> **Note on rotation:** QTM delivers the 6DOF rotation as a column-major 3×3 matrix. ofxQTMRT converts it to oF's row-vector `ofMatrix4x4` convention. This has not yet been validated against live hardware — if a rigid body's axes appear mirrored, see the comment in `buildRigidBody()` in [src/ofxQTMRT.cpp](src/ofxQTMRT.cpp) (transpose the fill).

## Usage

```cpp
// ofApp.h
ofxQTMRT qtm;

// setup()
qtm.setup("192.168.0.1");   // QTM server ip (base RT port 22222 by default)
qtm.setScale(0.1);          // optional: mm -> cm

// update()
qtm.update();               // call once per frame; non-blocking

// draw()
for (size_t i = 0; i < qtm.getNumRigidBody(); i++) {
    const auto& RB = qtm.getRigidBodyAt(i);
    ofPushMatrix();
    ofMultMatrix(RB.getMatrix());
    ofDrawAxis(60);
    ofPopMatrix();
}
for (size_t i = 0; i < qtm.getNumMarker(); i++)
    ofDrawBox(qtm.getMarker(i), 8);
```

See [example/](example/) for a complete app.

## Units & coordinates

QTM streams positions in **millimetres** in QTM's own coordinate system. Use `setScale()` for uniform scaling or `setTransform()` for an arbitrary `ofMatrix4x4` (applied to every position and composed with body rotation), exactly like ofxNatNet.

## Build

The Qualisys SDK is compiled from source inside the addon (`libs/qualisys_cpp_sdk`), so there are **no prebuilt binaries to manage**.

- **Linux / macOS**: no extra dependencies.
- **Windows**: links `ws2_32` and `iphlpapi` (handled by `addon_config.mk`).
- Requires **C++14** (set in `addon_config.mk`).

Add `ofxQTMRT` to your project's `addons.make` and regenerate the project with the openFrameworks Project Generator.

## Advanced

